<TITLE> Shajahan Omar gets bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com) The High Court Wednesday granted former state minister Shahjahan Omar three months' bail in a illegal wealth case. The court has also stayed Shahjahan's conviction and prison term for the same period. The court at the same time ordered the government to explain why the conviction and sentence should not be scrapped. A Dhaka special court had sentenced the fugitive Shahjahan to 13 tears in prison in on May 14, 2008. The former state minister surrendered before the HC bench of justices Md Mozammel Hossain and Afzal Hossain on Wednesday and appealed for bail. Anticorruption Comission filed the graft case with Gulshan police station on Sept 28 2007. Barrister AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury conducted Wednesday's bail hearing on behalf of Shahjahan and advocate Abdul Aziz Khan represented the ACC. bdnew
